      "court_date": "2025-06-30 9:00 AM",
      "matters": "PETITION FOR LETTERS OF ADMINISTRATION, Appointment Under IAEA<br>Off Calendar Jun-30-2025 Continued To Jul-28-25 At 09:00 A.M. In Dept 204<br>MINI MINUTES: <br>Appearances: Thomas Wrobel appeared via zoom for and with Arthur Anthony Petitioner/Beneficiary (in person). <br>Fatmata Bangura  for and with Tito Sandee Objector (in person). <br><br>The Court from the outset of the hearing requested clarification whether the decedent was a citizen of Sierra Leone, Mr. Wrobel confirmed that she was a citizen of Sierra Leone. <br><br>Ms. Bangura stated that Ms. Sandee did not leave a will, that she has one adult disabled child she takes care of, that she has no interest in the family estate, and that she only wants the out-of-pocket funeral expenses she paid for. Ms. Bangura stated she paid 75% of the funeral expenses. <br><br>The Court will continue the matter so that the proper notice can be given to Sierra Leone Embassy in Washington, DC prior to the next hearing. <br><br>The matter is continued to July 28, 2025 at 9:00 a.m., in Dept. 204.   <br><br>Judge: Ross C. Moody. Clerk: A. Datt. Not reported.<br>",
